freeFormTabs.title: Default
freeFormTabs.content:
The free-form statblock can be divided into multiple tabs to group and display only relevant parts.

Tabs can be renamed or removed by right-clicking them to open up a context menu.

**Please Note:** You can use [markdown syntax](https://www.markdownguide.org/cheat-sheet/) to write headlines, lists, links, tables and many other things.

freeFormTabs.title: Input
freeFormTabs.content:
Inputs allow you to easily keep track of information like HP and spell slots that changes frequently.

To create an input write i and an opening square bracket followed by a unique key for the information you want to track and a closing square bracket.

i[hp]

You can modify the input by adding a [JSON](https://www.w3schools.io/file/json-cheatsheet/) into the square brackets after a ";"

Valid fields are "value", "label", "type" and all other attributes of a [HTML Input Element](https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_form_attributes.asp)

i[name;{"label":"Character Name","type":"text"}]

freeFormTabs.title: Display
Dice Notation
freeFormTabs.content:
If you write dice notations like "+5" or "1d6+3" it will be highlighted and you can simply click it to roll the dice.

To change which dice will be rolled when simply writing "+5" you can go to Settings/Gamesystem Settings.

You can even use the display syntax in dice notations:

i[str;{"label":"Strength Modifier", "value":4}]
i[prof;{"label":"Proficiency Modifier", "value":2}]

**Attack:** +{{str + prof}} to hit. Deal 1d12+{{str}} slashing damage.

### Supported Dice
* 1d4
* 1d6
* 1d8
* 1d10
* 1d12
* 1d20

freeFormTabs.title: Static Variables
freeFormTabs.content:
---
test: Hello World
skills:
  acrobatics: 4
  investigation: 2
---
Sometimes you might want to use values that are more static than HP. For cases like that you can use the "frontmatter" syntax shown above which uses [YAML](https://www.w3schools.io/file/yaml-cheatsheet-syntax/). 

It's important to put this syntax at the top but it doesn't matter in which tab you put it. You can than use the defined values just like input values. 

Test: {{test}} 

Acrobatics: +{{skills.acrobatics}}\
Investigation: +{{skills.investigation}}

freeFormTabs.title: Layouts
freeFormTabs.content:
You can change the layout of your content with block elements.

### Row
This will put all elements into the same row.
:::row
i[a]
i[b]
i[c]
i[d]
:::

### Grid
When creating a grid you can add a number to define the number of columns you want your elements to take up.

#### Two column grid
:::grid2
i[a]
i[b]
i[c]
i[d]
:::
#### Three column grid
:::grid3
i[a]
i[b]
i[c]
i[d]
:::
#### Four column grid
:::grid4
i[a]
i[b]
i[c]
i[d]
:::

nodes.text:
Welcome to the Fey-Gate FreeForm tutorial!

To get started switch to the "Play Mode" by clicking on the banner showing the dice at the top right or pressing the "4" key.

You can now select the token of the frog person by clicking it with your left mouse button.

Once you selected the token the token detail view will show up at the bottom left of your screen. Click the parchment icon at the bottom left to open the Stat Editor popup.

Within this editor you can build your character sheet. It's populated with tutorial content explaining the new capabilities further.
